Led. av Sv:es adv:samf. 18.
translated: Billing, Folke Kristofer, lawyer, Gothenburg, born December 22, 1886 in Jönköping, son of city planner in Gothenburg, architect Emil B. and Ida von Wowern. Married Gulli-Britta Hessler in 1933. Completed studies at Gothenburg's Realskola in 1906, received a law degree from Uppsala in 1911. Worked as a junior clerk in the Skånska hovrätt (Scanian Court of Appeals) in 1911, then as a district court judge in Rönnebergs, Onsjö and Harjagers doms in 1912 and 1913. Became a lawyer in Stockholm in 1914, then worked at the law firm of Dr. Philip Lemans in Gothenburg from 1914 to 1945. Member of the Swedish Bar Association since 1918.
